3.2 Credential Access — LSASS Dumping (MITRE T1003.001)
Following initial access, the attacker performed targeted reconnaissance of running processes to locate LSASS, then extracted credentials via the named pipe interface — a technique consistent with in-memory credential theft without writing lsass.dmp to disk.
 
